76561198038658349,Recommended,249360,9281782,"Posted: 27 February, 2014",all,SqueakyDolphin,"An interesting, in depth, and addicting game. This game looks at an interesting balance between control and simulation. You can give tasks to your survivors according to their ability and relationships, but there is little control over how they perform, or even what supplies they use. To an extent, this removal of control acts against the game, but it gives the game a layer of complexity, depth, and free form that isn't present in most simulations. It's difficult to see this game as anything other than a simulation, and anybody longing for more control over their characters (such as in XCOM) will find this game lacking.What I've said is bad about the game, mostly. Describing the game's qualities is difficult to interpret in words. It possesses a dynamic feel, where everything connects to everything else, and challenges players to focus on the intricacies that aren't specified. The game is unforgiving and extremely challenging, which I feel accurately represents a zombie survival situation more effectively than most other games.Some ideas for updates would make this game really awesome. One idea is to present the player with a floor plan of each building, showing which rooms have been searched, as well as the locations of doors and windows. This will allow players to think much more strategically. Another idea is to provide some form of gameplay, maybe even minigames, which would allow players to have more control over the outcomes of certain events, such as assault, barricade construction, or defense. While the simulation feel of characters doing these tasks on their own is fine, without some form of control in these areas the majority of the gameplay revolves around text.Overall, a very good game, and I definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a realistic simulation of a zombie survival."
