76561198085086713,Recommended,249360,9742861,"Posted: 6 April, 2014",all,Independentrayz,"For those who are willing to lose... a lot.So...where to begin? For every game, it will have its pros and cons. For every player, it's up to them to decide what a game's pros and cons are. This review was made to (hopefully) make you decide whether you should buy this game or not. So without anymore delays, long and interesting sentences, long agonizing vocabulary words, and delays...  Let's start with the pros of the game!Overall, this game is astounding, repetive, and challenging. This game is based on strategy and randomly generated scenarios (mostly RNG).  Every desision you make can and will affect the situation your survivors have in any way possible. Whether choosing to inject yourself with a zombie ""cure"" (if you find it) or not, to let a little girl inside your safe house or not, or to kill one of your infected surviors or let them live in hopes of finding that cure (RNG could just straight out kill them if it wanted to). One of the best things about this game are the customization options. This game allows you to create your own survivors. Not only that, you can also customize and create your own occupations, locations, even gear! In my opinion, the best thing about this game is the idea of reading your survivors' story/diary. Whether they became trapped and met their awesome demise, or became one of the lucky ones who made it out of that dreaded city alive to tell the story. Now, I believe this game has the capabilities of being a best seller, however like every game, when there are pros, there are also cons.First of all, you must be accustomed to the fact that you will lose... a lot. It is a tendency to lose in almost every game you will play. No matter how ""good"" your group is well armed or skilled, you WILL lose. I, myself, have played this game hundreds of times... HUNDREDS! And out of those dreadful hours of losing and preparation, I only beat it fairly... ONCE. And by fairly, I meant getting the achievements I earned so far in this game by using the characters the game gave me, and abusing the save system like a ♥♥♥♥♥. Even if I would use my generated characters and their OP skills, my group would somehow end up being mauled by zombies, shot to death by crazed survivor groups, or being infected and dying from the virus. Survivor relations are also an issue because of the constant stress, arguements, and paranoia that will diminish one of your group member's relations with the rest of your group into hating each other instead of the zombies.Every so often, I check the statistics of this game (which I will put the link below) to see what the average win/ losses are worldwide. Some days I read that +40% of people killed an old lady that offered to trade supplies with them. Other days, +30% players had their group ditch one of their members in a room full of zombies to save the rest. These statistics show the amount of frustation, determination, and willingness to survive and complete their objective, even if it means to screw other people if it risks killing the rest of the group. Personally, I would have quit my current game or reverted to a previous save if a survivor died because it would just seem wise to do so (also because I'm a perfectionist)Overall, this game has pros and cons in terms of game play and survival. If I would rate this game, I would rate it an 7/10 because of the interesting factors and potenial. However, success in each game is heavily weighed on RNG.Link to Zafehouse: Diaries statisics:http://www.zafehouse.com/bodycount/"
