,Not Recommended,249360,8583339,"Posted: 5 January, 2014",all,ZodGilla,"As you'd expect from the Z in the title, Zafehouse Diaries is a game about zombies. The game is similar to a rogue-like in its random nature; the town is randomized, your survivors are randomized, loot is randomized, etc. so that no two playthroughs are exactly the same. Or so it should be.You'll find yourself in the usual boring, dreary town with a bunch of useless, racist, janitor survivors that will break each others arms and legs for refusing to play a game of chess (Not kidding). Even worse, you can even end up with Survivors that aren't good at anything at all, and you're stuck with them. If a Survivor dies, they are dead, and you wont be getting another. Expect to be given the short end of the straw many times, and to see the same stock photos for your survivors over and over.The game is too randomized. Everything you do feels like a roll of the dice in the zombies favor. Trying to fight a number of zombies above ten, even with all your survivors armed to the teeth, is certain suicide. Chances are slim you'll be able to clear the hospital or police station, with the horde's numbers varying from 10 to 20, and even higher. Even then, trying to clear out locations is a hassle. First, you must send out a scout to check out how many zombies are outside and how many zombies are inside. You'll have to go by what they say, because even though they may have seen eight zombies inside, there are actually twenty-three. Now that you have the place scouted out, you'll need to Assault it. This consists of your survivors trekking over to the location through the city, and the murdering every zombie outside and shooting through the windows inside. More than likely, you wont get all the zombies inside. Finally, you'll need to Breach. Your survivors will go back to the location for the third time and make their way inside, where they will proceed to most definitely die - Or kill the zombies if you are immensely lucky.Overall, the game just feels unfinished and unfair. There isn't much to do besides explore buildings, clear out buildings, try to escape, and survive. Weapon variety is dismal, with most melee weapons being absolute garbage and ranged weapons being entirely too risky to use, lest more than ten zombies surround your 'base' and you have no way to get out. Zafehouse Diaries is a good idea, but it  still feels like an alpha game and not a complete product.The only thing I really, really enjoy about the game is the journal, although it's severely flawed as you will see the same messages over and over again. When it rains, the journal pages get wet and the sound of rain on the roof fills your ears. When it thunders, light flashes on the screen as it storms outside. When you fight, blood splatters the pages.Good ideas but with poor implementation. I strongly advise you to buy this at a largely reduced price, at least 4.99."
