76561197962973671,Recommended,249360,17862939,"Posted: 3 September, 2015",all,Past0ri,"A different way of portraying a zombie apocalypse. In this game you control 1-5 survivors, by giving them different tasks, in order to survive.The course of the adventure is displayed in the pages of a diary. Every looted item, every killed zombie, every breached building, all the things happening emerge in the form of letters. I thought this must be boring as hell, but its not.Theres certain amount of excitement when you anticipate next moves of your survivors, who are most certaintly annoyed of one another, and they will fight each other. You can release the tensions in your group by spreading rumours of certain persons charity work or affiliation in crime or you can have bottle of spirits, maybe even a chess board or guitar in inventory.The gameplay area is randomly generated, with several different buildings. There are also rare random events, with positive and/or negative side effects.There are 3 different game modes, easy being the ""easiest"", where you start with only one survivor, so you could die in the first building you venture into, if not properly geared up. But you have infinite number of other survivors finding their way to you, and your only objective is to survive, with no timelimit. Some buildings also generate resources.In normal mode you start with 5 survivors, and your task is to find a vehicle, and then find several parts to repair it. There is no time limit, but there are more and more zombies spawning in the town when time passes. You cant replace survivors.Hard mode also starts with 5 survivors, who cannot be replaced, and must find an evacuation point. Time limit is set to 1 week.As a fan of zombie games, this 1 is a fresh breeze and welcomed addition, in the evergrowing line of zombie games. But... its very difficult to handle, has several balance issues and the survivors are not from the sharpest end of the pencil."
