76561198137225346,Recommended,249360,12825019,"Posted: 6 November, 2014",all,lordofgamez,"Zafehouse: Diaries isn't well known for it's moving pictures, but does keep you on your toes with it's survivor management gameplay! In-game, you're typically placed inside a set map filled with typical city buildings of importance; Hospitals, Bars, Houses, Police Stations, ect. You decide where you hold up base, and survive the onslaught of zombie ""X""'s on the map. But they aren't the only one's you'll be fighting out there... The game comes in three different modes, an easy mode which gives you one survivor, and no objective. You're able to signal for others to join your cause and live as a small little group for as long as you can. The medium and hard mode add objectives, as well as a time limit that you need to keep track of - among other problems. The biggest key feature in this is that you can add just about anyone you know into the game - slap in a picture and a persona and you're set! All you need to do after that is spend hours creating your own weapons and armor in the creator menu. Good luck my friend! You're going to need it!"
