,Recommended,249360,18664871,"Posted: 24 October, 2015",all,Omen UK,"Many may look at this game and think it doesn't look all that good, all that advanced, all that much fun, and they would be wrong.I'll admit I bought Zafehouse Diaries on a whim and I am so glad I did, I am really enjoying playing it.  You have three difficulty options ranging from a casual if still deadly walk-through to a complete Walking Dead, doing everything it takes to survive difficulty and accordingly the challenges you will face are more difficult too to match the level.  The game premise itself is fairly simple, you start off in a building and are required to fortify it, while fighting off hoardes of zombies, other survivors, and each other and are required to search other buildings for supplies, and information about an impeding escape or for parts for the car you hope to fix up to escape (depending ont he level you play).  It is a interesting addictive gameplay, one wrong move can mess up you're game and decimate your survivors but then too cautious  and you risk starving to desk.The ability to customize characters, professions, items (you can find) and some of the in-game pictures is a really great touch too, and while it would be nice to have a few more customizations to add categories of items in it doesn't detract from the variety you have through the customization. Added to this is the is the ability to edit your diary after the game ends which allows you to add a few more details too.Would recommend this game if you're looking for something different to play and hope. Even though they are going on to bigger, better, and moremore advanced projects I really hope Screwfly Studios continue with this game or make a follow up, i did enjoy it that much!!."
