76561198037461838,Not Recommended,249360,8490441,"Posted: 1 January, 2014",all,gabehuhlife,"This is not a typical zombie killing game. You do not directly kill zombies nor there is any strategic element in killing zombies. You are, for the lack of better word, the team spirit of the survivors and everything is more or less left to chances.It is a semi-realistic take on a zombie genre... in third person, which gives you the illusion of control along with the frustration that comes with it. You must watch the relationships between the survivors, food level and medical supplies among others. You must guide the survivors through the zombie infested town towards their salvation, which often feels like herding cats.I am not saying Zafehouse is a bad game. Zafehouse is an unique game that offeres a very different experience from other zombie games. It is just not for someone who expects more traditional zombie killing games. I can see how this game can be fun and engaging for some gamers but if you are a casual gamer who just wants to kill zombies like myself, do not buy this game.If, however, you are curious about this game, I suggest that you download the demo version before purchasing this game."
