76561198051710506,Recommended,249360,13426908,"Posted: 17 December, 2014",all,youngstr8,"Such a simple concept of zombie survival games, Survive and escape. Zafehouse: Diaries expands this, adding survivor skills, qualities, and the horror of a group collapsing in on each other. The greatest qualities are the randomization of your map, the three successful difficulty variations, and the personal customizations you can add to each time you play. Customizations like creating your own survivors and their occupations, locations on the map, weapons and tools to assist in your survival.Now the few issues in this game. The inability to assign equipment can be an issue when defending or going on patrol, slightly annoying but it is best to stay quiet and hidden from zombies anyway. Another problem is the unrelenting force of zombies that'll attack after accidentally using unsilenced fire-arms, forcing you to relocate and wait until the coast is clear before returning for left behind supplies.Beyond those two issues involving equipment usage; I can't see any other issues with the gameplay. The game runs very smoothly and I haven't had any issues between my computer and the game itself. Easily one of my favorite games out there, I recommend it to anyone whose looking for a strategy game with a simple goal and challenges to test your resolve to achieve that goal."
